00:09:28.934 --> 00:09:30.600 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: I've so many
questions for you.

00:09:30.600 --> 00:09:34.290 align:middle line:84%
OK, so let's talk about what
happens to women's hormone

00:09:34.290 --> 00:09:35.610 align:middle line:90%
after childbirth.

00:09:35.610 --> 00:09:37.820 align:middle line:90%
Do they drop dramatically?

00:09:37.820 --> 00:09:39.820 align:middle line:84%
Does the sex hormones
drop dramatically?

00:09:39.820 --> 00:09:41.100 align:middle line:90%
What happens?

00:09:41.100 --> 00:09:42.960 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: They
do drop dramatically.

00:09:42.960 --> 00:09:45.550 align:middle line:84%
When you deliver
that beautiful baby,

00:09:45.550 --> 00:09:47.360 align:middle line:84%
and then you deliver
the placenta,

00:09:47.360 --> 00:09:51.620 align:middle line:84%
your hormones go from
sky high down to nothing,

00:09:51.620 --> 00:09:52.710 align:middle line:90%
and that is dramatic.

00:09:52.710 --> 00:09:54.540 align:middle line:84%
It's a preview of
coming attractions

00:09:54.540 --> 00:09:58.800 align:middle line:84%
because you are in a
reversible menopausal state,

00:09:58.800 --> 00:10:00.350 align:middle line:84%
so a lot of women
don't realize this.

00:10:00.350 --> 00:10:04.660 align:middle line:84%
When I had my first baby,
I was sitting in my bed

00:10:04.660 --> 00:10:08.020 align:middle line:84%
breastfeeding, probably at
3:00 AM, sweating like a pig.

00:10:08.020 --> 00:10:09.714 align:middle line:84%
I was having hot
flashes, night sweats--

00:10:09.714 --> 00:10:11.130 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: And you
were in your 30s?

00:10:11.130 --> 00:10:14.150 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: I was in my
30s, and I was like, oh,

00:10:14.150 --> 00:10:15.400 align:middle line:90%
I have no hormones.

00:10:15.400 --> 00:10:16.620 align:middle line:90%
I have no sex hormones.

00:10:16.620 --> 00:10:18.570 align:middle line:84%
My estrogen is zero,
my progesterone

00:10:18.570 --> 00:10:21.010 align:middle line:84%
is zero, and the longer
that you breast feed,

00:10:21.010 --> 00:10:23.620 align:middle line:84%
the longer you stay suppressed
with your sex hormones.

00:10:23.620 --> 00:10:26.272 align:middle line:84%
So that's one of the reasons
why women who have a baby

00:10:26.272 --> 00:10:27.730 align:middle line:84%
really don't have
a lot of interest

00:10:27.730 --> 00:10:30.280 align:middle line:90%
in sex for quite a long time.

00:10:30.280 --> 00:10:31.794 align:middle line:84%
So your hormones
definitely drop.

00:10:31.794 --> 00:10:33.210 align:middle line:84%
The other thing
that's interesting

00:10:33.210 --> 00:10:36.670 align:middle line:84%
when it comes to
cortisol is that women

00:10:36.670 --> 00:10:40.690 align:middle line:84%
who are depleted, who
are pushers and musters

00:10:40.690 --> 00:10:43.119 align:middle line:84%
and just have sort
of overachievement

00:10:43.119 --> 00:10:44.660 align:middle line:84%
as part of their
motto-- I'm sure you

00:10:44.660 --> 00:10:45.660 align:middle line:90%
know nothing about this.

00:10:45.660 --> 00:10:47.920 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: I was just
going to say that word.

00:10:47.920 --> 00:10:48.880 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:10:48.880 --> 00:10:52.080 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: So women who are
really depleted in cortisol--

00:10:52.080 --> 00:10:54.080 align:middle line:84%
remember, you can either
be too high or too low,

00:10:54.080 --> 00:10:56.190 align:middle line:84%
or even both within
the same day.

00:10:56.190 --> 00:11:00.110 align:middle line:84%
Women who are low actually
feel better in pregnancy

00:11:00.110 --> 00:11:03.480 align:middle line:84%
because they share a
circulation with their baby, who

00:11:03.480 --> 00:11:05.450 align:middle line:90%
has perfect adrenal glands.

00:11:05.450 --> 00:11:08.650 align:middle line:84%
And so they have normal cortisol
levels during pregnancy,

00:11:08.650 --> 00:11:10.540 align:middle line:84%
and then when they
deliver their baby,

00:11:10.540 --> 00:11:14.730 align:middle line:84%
often the cortisol goes from a
normal level down to low level

00:11:14.730 --> 00:11:18.110 align:middle line:84%
again, and that can feel
like postpartum depression.

00:11:18.110 --> 00:11:20.060 align:middle line:84%
So we want to be
thinking hormones

00:11:20.060 --> 00:11:21.840 align:middle line:84%
whenever there's
depression, even

00:11:21.840 --> 00:11:23.461 align:middle line:90%
if it's postpartum depression.

00:11:23.461 --> 00:11:25.710 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: If you're stressed
out during your pregnancy,

00:11:25.710 --> 00:11:27.720 align:middle line:84%
this is a little of
a diversion here,

00:11:27.720 --> 00:11:31.520 align:middle line:84%
can you literally rob cortisol
from the baby's adrenal glands?

00:11:31.520 --> 00:11:34.050 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: Well, your baby
is very good at taking care

00:11:34.050 --> 00:11:35.940 align:middle line:90%
of itself.

00:11:35.940 --> 00:11:38.960 align:middle line:84%
We have enough places where
we make women feel guilty,

00:11:38.960 --> 00:11:40.530 align:middle line:84%
so I don't think
we have evidence

00:11:40.530 --> 00:11:43.315 align:middle line:84%
here that we're actually
robbing the poor baby

00:11:43.315 --> 00:11:46.330 align:middle line:90%
of its adrenal supply.

00:11:46.330 --> 00:11:50.690 align:middle line:84%
But we do have some evidence
that the amount of stress

00:11:50.690 --> 00:11:56.220 align:middle line:84%
you experience in utero
can shorten your longevity.

00:11:56.220 --> 00:11:58.315 align:middle line:84%
So we have evidence
with telomeres--

00:11:58.315 --> 00:12:00.940 align:middle line:84%
with those cute little caps that
are on your chromosomes, which

00:12:00.940 --> 00:12:03.550 align:middle line:84%
are the best marker of
biological as opposed

00:12:03.550 --> 00:12:05.000 align:middle line:90%
to chronological aging.

00:12:05.000 --> 00:12:07.780 align:middle line:84%
We have evidence that your
telomeres can shorten,

00:12:07.780 --> 00:12:10.900 align:middle line:84%
which is not a good thing,
when you're in utero if you're

00:12:10.900 --> 00:12:12.826 align:middle line:84%
under a lot of
stress, high cortisol.

00:12:12.826 --> 00:12:13.700 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: My goodness.

00:12:13.700 --> 00:12:19.040 align:middle line:84%
So you mentioned that you
were an MIT trained biohacker.

00:12:19.040 --> 00:12:21.840 align:middle line:90%
What exactly is that?

00:12:21.840 --> 00:12:24.790 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: Well, I happened
to do a physician scientist

00:12:24.790 --> 00:12:29.850 align:middle line:84%
training program at the Harvard
MIT, kind of combination.

00:12:29.850 --> 00:12:32.150 align:middle line:84%
So they came together
to do a special program

00:12:32.150 --> 00:12:33.990 align:middle line:84%
for folks who wanted
to go into academics

00:12:33.990 --> 00:12:35.800 align:middle line:90%
and be physician scientists.

00:12:35.800 --> 00:12:38.550 align:middle line:84%
So I did my training
in that setting,

00:12:38.550 --> 00:12:43.440 align:middle line:84%
and I call myself a biohacker
mostly because, in my 30s,

00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:45.080 align:middle line:90%
I was a total train wreck.

00:12:45.080 --> 00:12:47.330 align:middle line:90%
I had PMS, low sex drive.

00:12:47.330 --> 00:12:50.580 align:middle line:84%
I was about 25 pounds
heavier than I am now.

00:12:50.580 --> 00:12:52.940 align:middle line:84%
I blamed my husband
for most things,

00:12:52.940 --> 00:12:55.170 align:middle line:84%
and I was treating myself
with a glass or two

00:12:55.170 --> 00:12:58.270 align:middle line:84%
of wine every night,
which doesn't work.

00:12:58.270 --> 00:13:02.480 align:middle line:84%
And what I found was that,
when I went to my doctor

00:13:02.480 --> 00:13:07.150 align:middle line:84%
as many women do, I was
offered an antidepressant,

00:13:07.150 --> 00:13:09.180 align:middle line:84%
and that was a defining
moment for me, Lisa,

00:13:09.180 --> 00:13:12.260 align:middle line:84%
because I realized we're
treating these problems

00:13:12.260 --> 00:13:14.190 align:middle line:90%
with exactly the wrong things.

00:13:14.190 --> 00:13:16.180 align:middle line:84%
I had a hunch that my
problem was hormonal,

00:13:16.180 --> 00:13:18.670 align:middle line:84%
and it turns out that my
cortisol was about three times

00:13:18.670 --> 00:13:19.900 align:middle line:90%
where should have been.

00:13:19.900 --> 00:13:22.070 align:middle line:84%
And I fixed that
within about a month.

00:13:22.070 --> 00:13:23.570 align:middle line:84%
When I did that,
everything changed.

00:13:23.570 --> 00:13:25.100 align:middle line:90%
I lost weight.

00:13:25.100 --> 00:13:26.380 align:middle line:90%
I loved my husband again.

00:13:26.380 --> 00:13:27.000 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: You didn't have--

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:28.500 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: My
sex drive improved.

00:13:28.500 --> 00:13:29.860 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: --the antidepressant?

00:13:29.860 --> 00:13:32.700 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: I didn't
need the antidepressant.

00:13:32.700 --> 00:13:33.992 align:middle line:90%
We live in a culture that is --

00:13:33.992 --> 00:13:34.950 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Overprescribed.

00:13:34.950 --> 00:13:36.100 align:middle line:90%
>> GOTTFRIED: --in love

00:13:36.100 --> 00:13:39.750 align:middle line:84%
with masking symptoms
with pharmaceuticals,

00:13:39.750 --> 00:13:42.470 align:middle line:84%
and I really feel like the
way you eat, move, think,

00:13:42.470 --> 00:13:44.900 align:middle line:84%
and supplement is so
much more powerful.

00:13:44.900 --> 00:13:46.500 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: Absolutely,
we are, yes,

00:13:46.500 --> 00:13:49.090 align:middle line:84%
and this is the power
that you give us,

00:13:49.090 --> 00:13:53.660 align:middle line:84%
is information and how to find
out how to lower that cortisol.

00:13:53.660 --> 00:13:57.360 align:middle line:84%
So you described, what I
love in this next video,

00:13:57.360 --> 00:13:59.990 align:middle line:90%
is the typical Western women.

00:13:59.990 --> 00:14:04.670 align:middle line:84%
I eat too much, I drink
too much, I diet too much,

00:14:04.670 --> 00:14:07.330 align:middle line:84%
I don't sleep enough,
and then I give too much.

00:14:07.330 --> 00:14:09.750 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, that is the
typical Western woman.

00:14:09.750 --> 00:14:13.920 align:middle line:84%
So is that what is
causing our stress,

00:14:13.920 --> 00:14:16.830 align:middle line:84%
is overgiving,
overachieving, overdoing,

00:14:16.830 --> 00:14:18.350 align:middle line:90%
and then under doing?

00:14:18.350 --> 00:14:22.250 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: Well, I agree that
women are wired to overprovide.

00:14:22.250 --> 00:14:24.510 align:middle line:84%
We're wired to be
people pleasers.

00:14:24.510 --> 00:14:26.281 align:middle line:84%
Now, there's a few
notable exceptions,

00:14:26.281 --> 00:14:28.030 align:middle line:84%
but for the most part,
this is the problem

00:14:28.030 --> 00:14:29.880 align:middle line:84%
of every woman I
know, and it's one

00:14:29.880 --> 00:14:32.270 align:middle line:84%
of the reasons why we drive
ourselves into the ground.

00:14:32.270 --> 00:14:34.030 align:middle line:90%
Stress favors men.

00:14:34.030 --> 00:14:37.000 align:middle line:84%
I'm a feminist, so it
pains me to even say that.

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:40.350 align:middle line:84%
Our system, like our control
system, kind of the government

00:14:40.350 --> 00:14:42.450 align:middle line:84%
and how it talks
to our adrenals,

00:14:42.450 --> 00:14:45.070 align:middle line:84%
that system is a lot
more vulnerable in women

00:14:45.070 --> 00:14:46.010 align:middle line:90%
than it is in men.

00:14:46.010 --> 00:14:49.360 align:middle line:84%
That's why insomnia is twice as
high in women as it is in men.

00:14:49.360 --> 00:14:51.240 align:middle line:84%
That's why mood problems
are more common.

00:14:51.240 --> 00:14:54.237 align:middle line:84%
And so we want to
think about how can we

00:14:54.237 --> 00:14:55.320 align:middle line:90%
approach this differently.

00:14:55.320 --> 00:14:57.860 align:middle line:84%
The mantra of the
Western woman, I believe,

00:14:57.860 --> 00:15:01.510 align:middle line:90%
is the mantra of low oxytocin.

00:15:01.510 --> 00:15:05.840 align:middle line:84%
So oxytocin is this lovely,
happy brain chemical,

00:15:05.840 --> 00:15:08.960 align:middle line:84%
happy hormone, that does
many important things.

00:15:08.960 --> 00:15:11.360 align:middle line:84%
In fact, I think it's
nature's best hormone therapy.

00:15:11.360 --> 00:15:15.640 align:middle line:84%
It lowers your cortisol,
it raises your estradiol,

00:15:15.640 --> 00:15:18.080 align:middle line:84%
and it makes your
thyroid more efficient.

00:15:18.080 --> 00:15:22.230 align:middle line:84%
So it's a lovely hormone
and neurotransmitter

00:15:22.230 --> 00:15:23.710 align:middle line:90%
for men and women.

00:15:23.710 --> 00:15:25.580 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: Oh, men produce
oxytocin as well?

00:15:25.580 --> 00:15:26.160 align:middle line:90%
>> GOTTFRIED: Yes.

00:15:26.160 --> 00:15:27.451 align:middle line:90%
And you know, it's interesting.

00:15:27.451 --> 00:15:31.310 align:middle line:84%
It's also playing a big role
with social affiliation,

00:15:31.310 --> 00:15:33.880 align:middle line:84%
so folks who have
autism and schizophrenia

00:15:33.880 --> 00:15:36.230 align:middle line:84%
seem to have problems
with oxytocin.

00:15:36.230 --> 00:15:40.890 align:middle line:84%
It tends to lead to people being
more isolated, more online,

00:15:40.890 --> 00:15:44.790 align:middle line:84%
more depressed,
and so that's why

00:15:44.790 --> 00:15:47.370 align:middle line:90%
this is the latest party drug.

00:15:47.370 --> 00:15:49.100 align:middle line:84%
I think oxytocin is
really important.

00:15:49.100 --> 00:15:51.400 align:middle line:84%
It's important to amplify
the positive in the body,

00:15:51.400 --> 00:15:52.879 align:middle line:84%
and oxytocin is a
big part of that.

00:15:52.879 --> 00:15:55.170 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: But oxytocin is
something that you can't take,

00:15:55.170 --> 00:15:55.560 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:15:55.560 --> 00:15:57.650 align:middle line:84%
It's something that's produced
naturally from within you,

00:15:57.650 --> 00:15:58.050 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:15:58.050 --> 00:15:59.299 align:middle line:90%
>> GOTTFRIED: You can take it.

00:15:59.299 --> 00:16:02.060 align:middle line:84%
I'm not a fan of that because
the data is actually not

00:16:02.060 --> 00:16:04.900 align:middle line:84%
very convincing that it's
worthwhile to take it.

00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:07.590 align:middle line:84%
There's some physicians who
advocate taking oxytocin

00:16:07.590 --> 00:16:13.530 align:middle line:84%
to augment orgasm or to help
with this social isolation

00:16:13.530 --> 00:16:15.440 align:middle line:90%
that men, especially, have.

00:16:15.440 --> 00:16:17.590 align:middle line:84%
But what I've found
from the evidence

00:16:17.590 --> 00:16:22.080 align:middle line:84%
is that it's better to raise
your own endogenous oxytocin,

00:16:22.080 --> 00:16:23.950 align:middle line:90%
and you can do that with a hug.

00:16:23.950 --> 00:16:27.280 align:middle line:84%
So based on the half
life of oxytocin,

00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:29.150 align:middle line:84%
you want to hug
eight times a day,

00:16:29.150 --> 00:16:34.397 align:middle line:84%
and not just like the social
hug that is not a big deep hug.

00:16:34.397 --> 00:16:35.480 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: A hello hug, yes.

00:16:35.480 --> 00:16:37.855 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: We're talking
about like the Obama Michelle

00:16:37.855 --> 00:16:41.944 align:middle line:84%
hug on election night, like that
full on, hold it for a while.

00:16:41.944 --> 00:16:43.610 align:middle line:84%
You have to hold men
for a little longer

00:16:43.610 --> 00:16:46.740 align:middle line:84%
than you have to hold a woman
for the same spike in oxytocin.

00:16:46.740 --> 00:16:48.060 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Oh, interesting.

00:16:48.060 --> 00:16:48.930 align:middle line:90%
Very interesting.

00:16:48.930 --> 00:16:51.540 align:middle line:84%
So I'm sure most men
that are watching

00:16:51.540 --> 00:16:54.620 align:middle line:84%
were wondering, when you said
that the sex hormone drop

00:16:54.620 --> 00:16:57.570 align:middle line:84%
after breastfeeding and
childbirth, when do they ever

00:16:57.570 --> 00:16:58.490 align:middle line:90%
come back?

00:16:58.490 --> 00:17:00.490 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: Well, they
do gradually come back,

00:17:00.490 --> 00:17:04.460 align:middle line:84%
so if you stop breastfeeding
and you get back to kind

00:17:04.460 --> 00:17:06.470 align:middle line:84%
of business as
usual in your body,

00:17:06.470 --> 00:17:08.430 align:middle line:90%
you reclaim these hormones.

00:17:08.430 --> 00:17:12.680 align:middle line:84%
Now, starting between
35 and 45 for women,

00:17:12.680 --> 00:17:14.670 align:middle line:90%
you run out of ripe eggs.

00:17:14.670 --> 00:17:16.500 align:middle line:84%
So there's certainly
women who have

00:17:16.500 --> 00:17:19.230 align:middle line:84%
babies well into their
40s, but when you run out

00:17:19.230 --> 00:17:22.410 align:middle line:84%
of ripe eggs, that's when your
sex hormone start to change.

00:17:22.410 --> 00:17:25.810 align:middle line:84%
So that's when progesterone
starts to drop first,

00:17:25.810 --> 00:17:27.930 align:middle line:84%
and that's kind of
like nature's Valium.

00:17:27.930 --> 00:17:29.489 align:middle line:84%
It's really important
for soothing.

00:17:29.489 --> 00:17:30.530 align:middle line:90%
>> LISA: Progesterone is?

00:17:30.530 --> 00:17:32.530 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: Progesterone,
and so progesterone,

00:17:32.530 --> 00:17:35.360 align:middle line:84%
as that starts to drop,
your sleep can get worse.

00:17:35.360 --> 00:17:38.710 align:middle line:84%
You may notice that your periods
get a little closer together.

00:17:38.710 --> 00:17:40.710 align:middle line:84%
Then the second phase
of perimenopause,

00:17:40.710 --> 00:17:46.080 align:middle line:84%
typically 45 to 50 or 55, is
when estrogen starts to drop.

00:17:46.080 --> 00:17:49.620 align:middle line:84%
So if you have a baby-- I
had my first child at 32,

00:17:49.620 --> 00:17:52.960 align:middle line:84%
and my hormones went back to
normal within about a year.

00:17:52.960 --> 00:17:54.780 align:middle line:90%
I breastfed for about a year.

00:17:54.780 --> 00:17:58.180 align:middle line:84%
>> LISA: OK, and then so you
mentioned something called

00:17:58.180 --> 00:17:58.800 align:middle line:90%
sexopause.

00:17:58.800 --> 00:18:00.720 align:middle line:84%
You said perimenopause,
menopause,

00:18:00.720 --> 00:18:02.156 align:middle line:90%
but what is sexopause.

00:18:02.156 --> 00:18:05.870 align:middle line:84%
>> GOTTFRIED: Sexopause is when
you notice either a gradual

00:18:05.870 --> 00:18:08.530 align:middle line:84%
deminution in the sex
that you're having,

00:18:08.530 --> 00:18:11.140 align:middle line:90%
or maybe it's more sudden.

00:18:11.140 --> 00:18:13.790 align:middle line:84%
For some folks, after
they have a baby,

00:18:13.790 --> 00:18:17.950 align:middle line:84%
they never really integrate
kind of these redefined roles,

00:18:17.950 --> 00:18:22.780 align:middle line:84%
